  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. The standard equation of a circle in the <span class=\"italic\">xy</span>-plane is of the form <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, x minus h, close parenthesis, squared, plus, open parenthesis, y minus k, close parenthesis, squared, equals r squared\"></span>, where <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the ordered pair h comma k\"></span>&nbsp;are the coordinates of the center of the circle and <span class=\"italic\">r</span> is the radius. The given equation can be rewritten in standard form by completing the squares. So the sum of the first two terms, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared, plus 20 x\"></span>, needs a 100 to complete the square, and the sum of the second two terms, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y squared, plus 16 y\"></span>, needs a 64 to complete the square. Adding 100 and 64 to both sides of the given equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, x squared, plus 20 x, plus 100, close parenthesis, plus, open parenthesis, y squared, plus 16 y, plus 64, close parenthesis, equals negative 20, plus 100, plus 64\"></span>, which is equivalent to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, x plus 10, close parenthesis, squared, plus, open parenthesis, y plus 8, close parenthesis, squared, equals 144\"></span>. Therefore, the coordinates of the center of the circle are <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 10 comma negative 8\"></span>.<p>Choices A, C, and D are incorrect and may result from computational errors made when attempting to complete the squares or when identifying the coordinates of the center.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
